added.title: Tower Renovation
added.description: Following the destruction of their Tower by Slade, the Titans go house hunting.

added.title: My Name Is Jose
added.description: The Titans have Raven give them new super powers but have a hard time adjusting.

added.title: The Power of Shrimps
added.description: Aqualad uses shrimps and prime rib to win back Raven.

added.title: The Responsible
added.description: Gumball and Darwin babysit Anais "responsibly", whilst "irresponsibly" flooding the house.

added.title: The Third
added.description: Gumball and Darwin spice up their friendship by introducing a third best friend.

added.title: The Debt
added.description: Gumball resolves to save Mr Robinson's life during Elmore's Senior Talent Show.

added.title: The Pressure
added.description: Gumball tries to save Darwin from being kissed by a girl.

added.title: The Painting
added.description: Principal Brown tries to "fix" Gumball's dysfunctional family.

added.title: Craig of the Campus
added.description: Craig is dragged along on a college tour, but quickly finds himself chasing after a creek legend.

added.title: Wheels Collide
added.description: Craig tries to bring together the fastest kids in the Creek, and accidentally creates a rivalry between the 10 Speeds and the Roller Derby Kids.

added.title: Modern-ish Stone Age Family
added.description: The Bears are invited to live with a family of cavemen but things get rocky when the bears teach the family about television.

added.title: Excalibear
added.description: On the Bears' visit to a medieval vegetable-village, Grizz starts to believe that he's the rightful king.

added.title: Meat House
added.description: The Bears and their new friend Squatter Otter attempt to live in mysterious house made of meat.

added.title: Pirate Parrot Polly
added.description: On their quest for hidden treasure, the Bears team up with Polly the Parrot Pirate.

added.title: Baby Bear Genius
added.description: Ice Bear receives an invitation to attend a prestigious school for baby geniuses… but Grizz and Panda do not.

added.title: Way Back Wendel
added.description: Courtney must deliberately lose a challenge or let the entire world go back in time. It's a really hard choice for her.

added.title: Stingin' in the Rain
added.description: When Chef gets locked outside in a storm, the kids mistakenly assume he's a robber and decide to protect the Daycare, by any means necessary.

added.title: Cartoon Realism
added.description: Gwen is frustrated by Beth's silly belief that cartoons are real, but they visit an animation studio and discover that Beth is right!

added.title: OWW
added.description: When the kids discover Chef's past as a disgraced pro wrestler, they invite his old tag team partner to help put on a charity show. But is the big match about re-union or re-venge?!?

added.title: Gobble Head
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Lambporcini
added.description: Apple and Onion are very happy with their sweet new matching designer outfits they bought from known scam-artist Street Dog. That's until Chicken Nugget mistakes them for something they are not.

added.title: Jerk Chicken
added.description: In pursuit of the American Dream, Apple and Onion start their own business. However, a rather troublesome customer stands in their way.

added.title: Open House Cookies
added.description: Jerk Chicken is selling his house and Apple and Onion have been showing a lot of interest which definitely has nothing to do with the delicious cookies out on offer.

added.title: World Cup
added.description: It's time to relax in the expensive massage chairs that Apple & Onion have rented for the month. It's also time for the Football (soccer) World Cup and Falafel's team, Egypt are in the tournament..

added.title: Win It or Bin It
added.description: Apple and Onion are about to take ownership of a brand new luxury penthouse apartment and be rid of their roof shack for ever! All they need is a good reference from a previous landlord… Falafel.

added.title: French Toasting
added.description: Lucy's suspicious behavior prompts Oscar and Hedgehog to investigate whether or not she's the kingpin of a secret society.

added.title: We'll Just Move the Stars
added.description: When an astrological mismatch threatens King and Puddle's wedding, Oscar and Hedgehog join them on a quest to ensure love conquers all.

added.title: The Filth
added.description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: The Clocktopus
added.description: In a peaceful coastal town, Ben must not only face the archaic antagonist Steam Smythe and his latest creation, the Clocktopus, but also his deepest, darkest fear: Squids!

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 3
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: Divided We Stand
added.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

added.title: Asteroid Blues
added.description: An asteroid is headed right for the kingdom, so Dr Fox leads the gang on a mission to save the kingdom by flying a rocket to the asteroid's surface and blowing it to bits with a huge bomb. But when they get there the gang finds the lonely asteroid is actually a super nice guy and don't want to blow him up.

added.title: The Big Trip
added.description: It's time for the gang's yearly vacation, but Hawk refuses to go, claiming the gang's vacations are never fun for him because the others are terrible at vacationing. Hawk only agrees to go if the gang pass his super-intense vacation training course.

added.title: Late Night Talky Time
added.description: The moon is bored of taking the nightshift, since everyone's always asleep. So Unikitty leads the gang in putting on an over-the-top late night talk show to keep the moon occupied.

added.title: Welcome to the Unikingdom
added.description: After Unikitty finds out that tourism is down in the Unikingdom, she recruits the gang to make a tourism video to inspire people to visit the kingdom. But after calamities come one after another, Unikitty begins to think the video is going to turn out to be a disaster. However the friends save the day with some creativity and manage to get a single tourist to visit. Mission accomplished!

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Members Only
added.description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

added.title: Nano of the North
added.description: It's raining in Townville, but this is more than just rain. These drops are actually microscopic robots tearing apart the city, and the girls must find a way to fight them on their own level.

added.title: Superfriends
added.description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

added.title: Witch's Crew
added.description: On Halloween Night, Morbucks summons a monster that she didn't expect.

added.title: The Gift
added.description: The girls must replace the Professor's Christmas present on Christmas Eve.

added.title: Oh, Daisy!
added.description: Buttercup is not a fan of Bubbles' newly created digital assistant.

added.title: Brain Freeze
added.description: When a mysterious new ice cream flavor takes Townsville by storm, the girls suspect there might be foul play.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Dog Hotel
added.description: With no place to stay while their cave gets fumigated, the Bears book a night at a hotel for dogs.

added.title: Bear Lift
added.description: To help raise money to save Darrell's store, the Bears use the stack as a taxi through a ride share app.

added.title: The Nom Nom Show
added.description: Things go awry while Nom Nom shoots his first television show. The Bears offer to help and appear on the show.

added.title: Ice Cave
added.description: Ralph takes over the cave and turns it into a snowy fortress where he reigns as king over the Bears and Charlie.

added.title: Spa Day
added.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

added.title: Worm Bin
added.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

added.title: Pool's Out for Summer
added.description: The boys go to the Aberdale Community Pool for a day of wet fun! While Jeff slowly wades in the shallow end, getting used to the water, Sumo tries to conquer the diving board, redeeming himself from last summer's bellyflop, and Clarence sneaks past the lifeguards into the hot tub for a boiling surprise.

added.title: The Big Game
added.description: Chad takes Clarence to his first big game! Clarence takes it all in - the crack of the bat, the touchdown dances, the slam-dunks and of course, hotdogs and popcorn! But will Clarence get to fulfill his dream of meeting Aberdale's beloved mascot?

added.title: The Boxcurse Children
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: The Little Mer-Tiger
added.description: The origin of Tiger is told as a flashback.  As the legend goes, Tiger used to be a mermaid.  One day the evil ruler of the sea, Bubble Grandpa, demanded a hamburger and picked Tiger to retrieve it.  He used his magic sea powers to give Tiger legs and send her ashore.  But Tiger grew to love the land, and with the help of her new friend, Uncle Grandpa, defeated the evil sea ruler and got to keep her legs.

added.title: Ballroom
added.description: MG fixes up the ballroom and warns UG and PS not to step a foot in there until he gets a chance to use it.  But UG mistakenly tosses a ball into the room.  Now PS and UG have to retrieve the ball without touching one foot to the ground.

added.title: Back to the Library
added.description: Uncle Grandpa uses time travel to convince his past self to return a library book on time.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Dia de profesionales
added.description: Después de un gasto excesivo, Golden Goose le dice a la pandilla que no les dará más huevos de oro hasta que aprendan el valor del dinero. Siguiendo el consejo de Rick de ahorrar dinero, la pandilla abrió una tienda de galletas para ganar dinero por su cuenta y guardarla en una gran bóveda.

added.title: Asteroide Triste
added.description: Un asteroide viaja directo hacia el reino, por lo que la Dra. Fox se pone al frente de la banda en una misión para volar en un cohete hasta la superficie del asteroide y hacerlo explotar en pedazos con una enorme bomba para así salvar el reino. Pero al llegar, la banda descubre que el asteroide solitario es en realidad un tipo sumamente agradable y se rehúsan a hacerlo explotar. Por desgracia, el asteroide se entera del plan de Fox y sale corriendo llorando, icon la bomba aún en su interior! La Dra. Fox, arrepentida, lleva de urgencia a la banda tras el asteroide para levantarle el ánimo antes de que sea demasiado tarde.

added.title: El gran viaje
added.description: Es hora de las vacaciones anuales de la banda, pero Halcondrilo se niega a ir, alegando que las vacaciones de la banda nunca son divertidas para él porque los otros son pésimos compañeros de vacaciones. De hecho, Halcondrilo solo acepta ir si la banda aprueba su curso de entrenamiento de vacaciones superintensivo: ilos desafíos temáticos más emocionantes que se puedan imaginar!

added.title: Bienvenidos al Unireino
added.description: Después de descubrir que el turismo escasea en el Unireino, Unikitty recluta a la banda para que hagan un video que inspire a la gente a visitar el reino. Pero luego de varias calamidades, Unikitty comienza a creer que el video resultará siendo un desastre. Sin embargo, los amigos salvan el día con algo de creatividad y logran hacer que un solo turista los visite. iMisión cumplida!

added.title: Charlas Nocturnas
added.description: La luna está aburrida de tomar el turno de noche, ya que todos siempre están dormidos. Entonces, Unikitty lidera a la pandilla en la presentación de un programa de entrevistas nocturno exagerado para mantener la luna ocupada.

added.title: La Suciedad
added.description: A Ben le encargan la tarea de limpiar la Chatarra, pero cuando, engañado por los viles villanos Fly Guys, permite que se lo roben, debe perseguirlos antes de que fabriquen una larva monstruosa imparable con un objetivo claro: destruir Las Vegas.

added.title: Filtro Acuatico
added.description: El viaje de Ben, Gwen y Max a las Cataratas del Niágara se ve interrumpido por los horribles Hydromanders: unas criaturas que los amenazan a ellos y a los demás turistas.

added.title: El Lider Del Ring
added.description: Cuando Ben tiene una racha ganadora en un videojuego, se le ocurre una idea para ganar un partido real de lucha, hasta que un luchador intimidante decide convertirlo en un verdadero desafío.

added.title: Sobreviviendo A La Tormenta
added.description: El campamento de Ben y Gwen se ve interrumpido por los gélidos Weatherheads -Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o-, pero un Omnitrix que funciona mal y dispara un montón de extraterrestres podría no ser un pronóstico de éxito.

removed.title: Toma 10
removed.description: Mientras Ben intenta rodar su propia película independiente, por accidente libera a una pandilla de insectos y, cuando la lucha se traslada a su guarida oculta, Ben debe enfrentarse a su líder narcisista: La Hormiga Reina.

removed.title: Shhh
removed.description: Mientras Ben se relaja en un monasterio con una política de silencio, no puede quedarse callado y, por accidente, despierta a un peligroso Dragón oculto en una recámara secreta bajo los salones sagrados...una tarea que podría ser demasiado para manejar, iincluso para Diamante!

removed.title: Cambio De Edad
removed.description: Durante una parada en la megatienda Shoppë, Nanny Nightmare -una niñera que se volvió loca- transforma a Ben y Gwen en bebés. Y nada la detendrá en su intento de reorganizar el mundo a imagen y semejanza de su guardería.

removed.title: La Breve Carrera De La Nina Suertuda
removed.description: Cuando un hechicero jugador de cosplay pone las manos sobre una varita mágica real en la convención Comic Con, Ben consigue la ayuda de Gwen para impedir que Hex la recupere: Gwen engaña al hechicero malvado y le hace creer que es una poderosa maga...ila única e inimitable Niña Suertuda!

removed.title: Ken 10
removed.description: We're back in the future with Ben 10K, and this time he has a son, Ken. On Ken's tenth birthday, Ben gives him his very own Omnitrix. Ben must come to learn to trust Ken with the power of the Omnitrix. Along the way, Ken befriends a kid named Devlin. Devlin turns out to be Kevin 11's son and was merely using Ken so he could break his dad out of the Null Void. Ben 10K and Ken then team up to take down Kevin 11. As for Devlin, he comes to realize his dad is a jerk, and realizes the error of his ways. He's able to redeem himself, proving he's a good kid and joining forces with "Team Tennyson."

removed.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
removed.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

removed.title: Ready to Rumble
removed.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

removed.title: Don't Drink the Water
removed.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

removed.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
removed.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.

removed.title: Shhh!
removed.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

removed.title: Animo Farm
removed.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

removed.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
removed.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

removed.title: Take 10
removed.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

removed.title: Growing Pains
removed.description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppe, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

removed.title: Bernard of the Creek Part 2
removed.description: Bernard joins up with the wrong crowd of Creek Kids, forcing Craig to take action to save his brother.

removed.title: Bernard of the Creek Part 1
removed.description: Craig is shocked when his older brother Bernard asks to join him at the Creek.

removed.title: Jelly Aches
removed.description: The school descends into chaos after getting a visit from Gazunga, the Jealousy Troll.

removed.title: Simply Perfect
removed.description: When the kids are about to be subject to school testing with no time to study, Courtney freaks and orders a Brainiac Ray from the back of a comic book that does not work as advertised.

removed.title: Snack to the Future
removed.description: Owen wants his favorite treat, Jiggle Giggle, so bad that he's willing to use a time machine to get to snacktime quicker. But when he ends up stuck in the past, Owen must decide between getting home and getting fed.

removed.title: Space Codyty
removed.description: Izzy, convinced that Cody is an alien, embarks on a journey through space to take him back home.

removed.title: Baby Brother Blues
removed.description: When Beth is told that the impending arrival of a baby brother is about to ruin her life, she runs away to find a new family.

removed.title: Fiesta Day
removed.description: The Bears party it up with a living piñatas for Fiesta Day. Wanting the festivities to never end, Grizz wishes for it to be Fiesta Day everyday.

removed.title: Snow Place Like Home
removed.description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

removed.title: Hashtag #1 Fan
removed.description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

removed.title: Baba Yaga House
removed.description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

removed.title: Bug City Sleuths
removed.description: To survive in a city inhabited by bugs, the Bears become noir-style detectives.
